    </div>
    <Image
      p-fragment
      src={dsc}
      alt="design system circle"
      class="alter-image-size"
    />
  </div>
  <PNotes>
    Using Atomic Design as a reference, we can define patterns and components as
    follows:
    <ul style="font-size: 1.5rem;">
      <li>
        <strong>Component library</strong>: a collection of reusable building
        blocks (atoms, molecules, and organisms). For example, a button, an
        input field, or even a modal.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Pattern library</strong>: a collection of common design
        solutions built from multiple components, used to solve recurring
        usability needs. For example, a navigation bar with a logo, links, a
        search form, and a CTA button.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Style guide</strong>: the foundation layer that defines colors,
        typography, spacing, and other visual rules of the system.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

